@node "INTRODUCTION" "P-Menu v1.1 (c) Trevor Rycraft"
                                ___ ___         ______         
                .-----. ______ |   Y   |.-----.|   _  \ .--.--.
                |  _  ||______||.      ||  -__||.  |   ||  |  |
                |   __|        |. \_/  ||_____||.  |   ||_____|
                |__|           |:  |   |       |:  |   |       
                               |::.|:. |       |::.|   |       
                               `--- ---'       `--- ---'       
                               ..PriVate mEnU...

                               ===============
                               = What is it? =
                               ===============

PMENU or Private Menu is a TRANSPARENT security menu door for your BBS.

If you want to keep certain people out of a certain menu(s) without them
actually KNOWING about it.. then heres the solution.  Pmenu is an invisible
door, when run it looks for a datafile called 'Doors:Pmenu/Pmenu.Users' with
users names in.

If the users name IS in there then it calls the specified menu (see @{"USAGE" link "USAGE" 0})
Alternatively as well as the above, if a file called 'Doors:Pmenu/Pass.Ansi'
exists then this file will be displayed
 FIRST! and then the menu called.          

IDEAL for changing security issues and informing the authorised users =)

OTHERWISE...

If the users name IS NOT in the datafile then it will just quit OR if
'Doors:Pmenu/NoAxs.Ansi' exists then this ansi file will be displayed first
and THEN quit.

(HINT: Make use or the %Z or %Y inserts - or if ya REALLY wanna be cheeky try
the %X ;)  
@endnode

@node "installation" "How To install Pmenu!"
 INSTALLATION:

    Simple, just unpack Pmenu.lha to DOORS:where a directory called
    'Doors:Pmenu/' will be created containing all the files. =)   
@endnode

